HEADWORD: Transformism
<hw>Trans*form"ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>transformisme</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The hypothesis,
or doctrine, that living beings have originated by the modification of
some other previously existing forms of living matter; -- opposed to
<xex>abiogenesis</xex>.</def> <rj><au>Huxley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

